        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-07-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-07-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="345" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d345">
                <head>No. 345.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">L. S.
                                    Sackville West</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-07-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 24, 1887</date>.
                                (Received July 26.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that I am
                            instructed by the Marquis of Salisbury to inform the United States
                            Government, in compliance with the provisions of article 34 of the
                            general act of Berlin, that, by a proclamation dated the 14th May last,
                            the whole of Zululand, including the territory known as the Zulu Reserve
                            Territory, but excluding the territory known as the New Republic, and
                            bounded as follows: On the north and southwest by the Colony of Natal,
                            on the west and north west by the New Republic; on the north by Amatonga
                            land, and on the east by the Indian Ocean, was declared to be a British
                            possession under the name of Zululand.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">L. S. Sackville
                            West.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
